.TH MANDOR 1 "2026-07-18" "mandor" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mandor \- the foreman for your containers: a tiny PID-1 process supervisor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mandor
[\fIflags\fR] [--] \fI"CMD"\fR [\fI"CMD"\fR ...]
.br
.B mandor report
[\fINAME\fR|\fIPID\fR] [\fB--json\fR]
.br
.B mandor report --incidents
[\fINAME\fR] [\fB--since=\fIDUR\fR] [\fB--incident=\fIN\fR]
.br
.B mandor report --cost
[\fB--json\fR]
.br
.B mandor validate
[\fB--config=\fIPATH\fR]
.br
.B mandor
[\fB--help\fR | \fB--version\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mandor
runs as PID 1 in a container, spawns worker processes, forwards signals,
reaps zombies, restarts what crashes, and\(emwhen a worker dies\(emwrites a
structured JSON incident bundle explaining what happened. It is a single
static binary (~230 KB), fully offline unless a network feature is configured.
.PP
Each \fICMD\fR is one worker: a quoted command line tokenized by mandor (no
shell required). Workers are named by the basename of their first token.
.SH COMMON FLAGS
.TP
.BR \-\-restart= never|on\-failure|always
Restart policy (default: never).
.TP
.BR \-\-config= PATH
Load a mandor.toml (default: ./mandor.toml if present).
.TP
.BR \-\-health= "\fINAME=CMD\fR"
Liveness probe for a worker (exit 0 = healthy). Repeatable.
.TP
.BR \-\-metrics= PORT
Serve Prometheus text metrics on 127.0.0.1:PORT.
.PP
Advanced flags (\fB--backoff-max\fR, \fB--stop-grace\fR,
\fB--expected-exit\fR, \fB--max-restarts\fR, \fB--state-dir\fR,
\fB--ready-fd\fR, \fB--on-incident\fR, \fB--photon\fR) and all TOML-only keys
are documented in \fBdocs/CONFIG.md\fR.
.SH SIGNALS
TERM/INT start graceful shutdown (forwarded to worker process groups; a
second signal or \fB--stop-grace\fR expiry escalates to KILL). HUP, QUIT,
USR1, USR2, and WINCH are passed through to workers.
.SH EXIT STATUS
The worst worker exit code (128+N for signal deaths), honoring
\fB--expected-exit\fR; the give-up, essential, or oneshot worker's code when
those mechanisms trigger; 2 for a configuration or startup error.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B MANDOR_STATE_DIR
State and incident spool directory (default: /var/lib/mandor).
.TP
.B MANDOR_RELEASE ", " GIT_SHA
Release identifier recorded in incident bundles.
.TP
.B PHOTON_TOKEN
Bearer token for photon OTLP forwarding.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I <state-dir>/state.json
Live worker status (read by \fBmandor report\fR).
.TP
.I <state-dir>/incidents/*.json
Incident bundles (newest 200 retained).
.TP
.I <state-dir>/cost.json
Per-worker resource-cost profiles (see \fBmandor report --cost\fR).
.TP
.I /dev/termination-log
When present (Kubernetes), receives the latest incident verdict.
.SH SEE ALSO
Project home and full documentation: https://github.com/asyafalni/mandor
